      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WENTWORTH FALLS (8) resumed from a long break in a richer maiden and tried to lead throughout but was swamped late. Fitter again and extra trip a plus. This is a weak maiden and gets chance. SACRE BLEU (3) ran on well fresh then was solid again last time when fourth at Pakenham latest. Should be at top now and on latest figure would go close. JUST BASIL (5) started big odds at Pakenham on debut and after bombing the start ran well enough. This easier and much better placed here. Can improve sharply. ELITE PETE (2) is a long time maiden who mixes form but has ability and the blinkers added for this. Worth including. MR MYRTLEVALE (6) ran on well late on debut and worth following up.",
